            <pb n="10" facs="#f0001"/>
            <p>It has lately been rumored that the celebrated<lb break="yes"/>Baron Humboldt is taking an interest in table-<lb break="no"/>turning and spirit rappings, and, accordingly, Dr.<lb break="yes"/>Jobard wrote a letter to the old savant, who re-<lb break="no"/>plied as follows:</p>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <div n="2">
                <dateline>
                    <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;<hi rendition="#k">Berlin,</hi> April 2, 1856.</hi>
                </dateline>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>&#x201C;<hi rendition="#k">Dear Sir:</hi> You wrote, as always, a most amiable<lb break="yes"/>letter, but I am unable to discuss the simple possibility<lb break="yes"/>of different kinds of mineral, vegetable, animal, vol-<lb break="no"/>untary and involuntary cerebral electricism. I had al-<lb break="no"/>ways the weakness of having a dread of the spiritual-<lb break="no"/>ism of pine deals and of psychographic mysticism. You<lb break="yes"/>augment my dread by the ghost of an ephemeral ra-<lb break="no" />tional being, which is to get understanding by the<lb break="yes"/>thoughts of the men surrounding the instrument (the<lb break="yes"/>mediums around the table). You know that Geoffroy<lb break="yes"/>de St. Hilaire believed he had in Egypt had a transpi-<lb break="no"/>ration of oxydated thoughts; and you, dear Doctor,<lb break="yes"/>will perhaps find that my skepticism is the result of my<lb break="yes"/>laziness. I submit to this rebuke, but I am conviaced<lb break="yes"/>that the regret which I feel in knowing that you have<lb break="yes"/>gone astray on such a dark pathway will not diminish<lb break="yes"/>the friendship which you have allowed me to enjoy for<lb break="yes"/>so long. I trust you will excuse me.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;ALEXANDER VON HUMBOLDT.&#x201D;</hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
        </body>
